<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,746,1532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,746,772]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small, pallid gray, variegated with brown on head, metopidium and base of posterior process. Suprahumeral horns abruptly acute to apex; lateral spines of posterior process short, conical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,746,1532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,381,826,852]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">Measurements</emphasis>
(mm). Male. Total length: 
<number box="[698,753,826,852]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" value="5.58">5.58</number>
; pronotal length 
<number box="[950,1005,826,852]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" value="4.5">4.50</number>
; tegmina length 5.00; width between humeral angles 
<number box="[335,390,866,892]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" value="1.64">1.64</number>
; width between apices of suprahumeral horns 
<number box="[930,985,866,892]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" value="2.64">2.64</number>
; maximum width between apices of of posterior process 
<number box="[357,412,906,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" value="1.52">1.52</number>
; head width 
<number box="[561,616,906,932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" value="1.6">1.60</number>
