<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,746,1532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,340,1466,1492]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">Comments.</emphasis>
This small pallid species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler" authorityName="Fowler" box="[770,1073,1466,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Poppea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis box="[770,980,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">Poppea reticulata</emphasis>
Fowler
</taxonomicName>
, however the posterior process is only weakly inflated. The lateral spines of posterior process are very short and straight in 
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1329,1507,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Poppea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1218,1329,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">P. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1336,1428,1506,1532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1336,1428,1506,1532]" pageId="6" pageNumber="58">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
